Below is a **complete, real‑world React + Cookies + JWT login example** that follows **industry best practices**:

✅ JWT **access token** (short‑lived)  
✅ **HttpOnly cookie** for refresh/session  
✅ Works across **refresh & new tabs**  
✅ **Secure against XSS & CSRF (baseline)**

I’ll show **Backend → Frontend → Flow explanation**.

***

# ✅ Architecture (IMPORTANT)

    Access Token  → Stored in React memory (JS)
    Refresh Token → HttpOnly Cookie (set by server)

✅ React **never reads** refresh token  
✅ Browser automatically sends cookie  
✅ This is how real enterprise apps work

***

