# 🔐 Security Breakdown (VERY IMPORTANT)

| Protection              | Enabled                    |
| ----------------------- | -------------------------- |
| HttpOnly refresh cookie | ✅                          |
| XSS token theft         | ❌ blocked                  |
| CSRF risk               | ✅ mitigated (SameSite=Lax) |
| JWT expiry              | ✅                          |
| Auto refresh            | ✅                          |

***

# ❌ What NOT To Do

❌ Store JWT in localStorage  
❌ Read refresh token in React  
❌ No `credentials: "include"`  
❌ Long‑lived access tokens

***

# ✅ Real‑World Summary (MEMORIZE)

✅ React handles UI + access token  
✅ Cookies handle session securely  
✅ Access token = memory only  
✅ Refresh token = HttpOnly cookie  
✅ This is enterprise‑grade auth

